						               													<description>The High Priest of the Order has passed away, after some good years of service, leaving the place vacant. Now the God-Emperor of Egypt must deliberate who will fill the position.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After a revealing dream, where the God-Emperor has a conversation with the God Khepri himself (Scarab God of Ancient Egypt), it is decided that the way of election must be by confronting the Priests to a battle of cunning and strategy that will leave one of them on top.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Khepri, players play the role of an aspiring Priest of the Order of Khepri. The winner of the game will be elected the new High Priest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Khepri is a board game for 2 to 4 PLAYERS, where there is no chance, therefore what prevails is strategy and logic. It is an abstract game where the number of players, per game, forces to change the strategy to win. Duration: 30 min. to 45 min.&amp;#10;The rules are very easy to learn, as they occupy only 1 sheet of paper. Three types of maneuvers, movement and how to score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has been completely designed by Pere Martinez, who already has some other experience in this game world, such as Kao.&amp;#10;For the magnificent illustration of the box and the design of the board we have counted on Amy Kitsune.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher (translated)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
